# Keep the Docker build context lean and — critically — keep the host's
# node_modules out of the image. The Dockerfile runs `pnpm install`
# inside the container to lay down Linux-native deps; a bare `COPY backend
# ./backend` would otherwise overwrite them with the host's (Windows) pnpm
# symlinks pointing at absolute host paths, so `tsx`/etc. become unresolvable.
# Exclude anything that isn't needed to RUN the backend in the container.

# Dependencies + build output (recreated in-image or not needed at runtime).
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/.astro/
**/.output/
**/build/

# Git + docs + design artifacts (not needed in the runtime image).
.git/
.gitignore
.github/
vibes/
docs/
deploy/
*.md

# Local env (compose injects env at runtime; never bake secrets into an image).
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Editor / OS cruft.
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local embedded-postgres data + logs (dev-only).
.pgdata/
*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*